                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.354,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has our opinion this morning in case 14-144, Walker v. Sons of Confederate Veterans."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.354,
                        "stop": 247.392,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.354,
                                "stop": 15.054,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Texas issues both ordinary license plates and specialty license plates."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.054,
                                "stop": 35.676,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now those who want the State to issue a particular specialty plate can propose to the State, a plate design which is a slogan and sometimes a graphic design, and in this case the Texas Department of Motor Vehicles Board rejected a proposed plate design that was submitted to them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.676,
                                "stop": 39.671,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The design featured the Confederate battle flag."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.671,
                                "stop": 50.929,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Texas division of the Sons of Confederate Veterans sued the Board claiming that the rejection of their design violated the First Amendment\u0027s Free Speech Clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.929,
                                "stop": 58.512,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals agreed, said it did violate the clause, we here review that determination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.512,
                                "stop": 65.543,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We hold that Texas\u2019 rejection of the Confederate flag design does not violate the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.543,
                                "stop": 74.172,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our analysis closely follows the analysis set forth in an earlier case of this court Pleasant Grove City v. Summum."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.172,
                                "stop": 93.698,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In that case we held a city \u201caccepting a privately donated monument putting it on a city property\u201d was engaging in what we have called government\u2019s speech, speech that government has broad leeway to decide when, whether and how to express."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.698,
                                "stop": 111.368,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In reaching that conclusion in the Summum case the Court considered the history of the government program and its purposes reflected on whether observers would recognize the government to be speaking and examine the government\u2019s control over the messages conveyed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.368,
                                "stop": 124.329,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Those same factors lead us to conclude in this case that Texas\u2019 specialty license plate designs fall into the same category namely government speech."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.329,
                                "stop": 137.998,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The history of license plates and we have a long history of the license plates in the world, I guess, shows that states have long used license plates in this country to convey government messages."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.998,
                                "stop": 159.802,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The speech appears on what looks like essentially a government issued identification such that a reasonable observer would associate the speech with the government indeed a driver could just as easily if he wanted to, express the same message just by putting it on a bumper sticker next to the license plate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.802,
                                "stop": 167.843,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Why would that driver want to put say a flag on the license plate rather than on the bumper?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.843,
                                "stop": 181.051,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Perhaps, because placing it on the license plate would suggest at least to some observers that it is the State that is conveying the message that the flag embodies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.051,
                                "stop": 192.399,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "An additional consideration is that the Texas statutory scheme gives the State final approval authority and thus control over specialty license plate designs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.399,
                                "stop": 207.341,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We also recognize as we have previously held that the First Amendment limits a State\u2019s authority to require a private party to display a license plate containing a government message with which the private party disagrees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.341,
                                "stop": 213.438,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Taking that earlier case together with today\u0027s case produces a kind of legal symmetry."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 213.438,
                                "stop": 224.24,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Just as Texas cannot force a private citizen to convey on his or her license plate a message with which he or she does not agree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.24,
                                "stop": 233.978,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So the Sons of Confederate Veterans cannot force Texas to convey on its license plates a message with which the State does not agree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.978,
                                "stop": 237.068,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Fifth Circuit is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.068,
                                "stop": 247.392,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has written a dissenting opinion in which he is joined by the Chief Justice and Justices Scalia and Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
